Toflania's ally Malaha avoided entering the war

Erstadia declared a war on its rival Lirah
Lirah's ally Sofrostia joined the war on defenders side

notes.legend: A geothermal springs with naturally heated water that provide relaxation and medicinal benefits. Average temperature is 29¬∞C.

notes.name: Kart Purifying Well
notes.legend: This legendary water source is whispered about in ancient tales and believed to possess mystical properties. The spring emanates crystal-clear water, shimmering with an otherworldly iridescence that sparkles even in the dimmest light.

notes.name: The Golden Inn
notes.legend: A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious fried cheese with grey nectar is served here.

notes.legend: Tipplers speak of a horrifying Cyclops who inhabits Rakku hills and prefers eating children.

notes.name: Peretsk Roc
notes.legend: Locals speak of a proud Roc who inhabits Peretsk hills and harasses travelers in the area.

notes.legend: Ruins of an ancient town. Untold riches may lie within.

notes.name: Ruined Fortress

notes.legend: Ruins of an ancient pyramid. Untold riches may lie within.

notes.name: Aslapayaya Library
notes.legend: A vast collection of knowledge, including many rare and ancient tomes.

notes.legend: Roll up, roll up, this unmissable circus is here for a limited time only.

notes.name: Vopengen Contest
notes.legend: Warriors from around the land gather for a contest of acumen in Vopengen, with fame, fortune and favour on offer to the victor.

notes.name: Badaat Fair
notes.legend: A fair is being held in Badaat, with all manner of local and foreign goods and services on offer.

notes.name: Minor Jetty
notes.legend: A small location along the Fjellveroy River to launch boats from sits here, along with a weary looking owner, willing to sell passage along the river.

notes.name: Falcons migration
notes.legend: A huge group of falcons are migrating, whether part of their annual routine, or something more extraordinary.

notes.name: Kamhonghoi jamboree
notes.legend: A jamboree has been organised at Kamhonghoi as a chance to gather the great and the good of the area together to be merry, make alliances and scheme around the crisis.

notes.name: Myrinesnes Cave
notes.legend: The Myrinesnes Cave. Locals claim that it is a good spot to hid treasure.

notes.name: Asingsbole Necropolis
notes.legend: A labyrinthine necropolis where each step echoes with haunting murmurs. The walls are adorned with ancient runes, and restless spirits guide or hinder those who dare to delve into its depths
